[The Philippines, which constitutes an archipelago of 7107 islands with a
total land area of about 300 000 sq km (116 000 sq mile), is divided into 3
main island groups: Luzon, Visayas and Mindanao; see map at
<http://www.supertravelnet.com/maps/?action=selmap&country=236_0_4&language=1>.
From previous postings on the current Ebola-Reston event and from the
above 4 collected newswires, it appears that -- so far -- ERV infection has
been detected in 2 locations in Luzon, namely in Pandi and Talavera town
outside Manila. It will be interesting to note on what grounds/tests has
absence of infection been declared in Visayas (which includes Negros
Occidentale; see item 3 above) or in any other part of the vast Philippines
territory.

The above newswires reflect the endeavors of the authorities to address
consumer concerns on the safety of pork. The active involvement of the 3
international organisations in the investigation efforts of this event is
commendable. Details on the sampling criteria applied for the collection of
the 600 samples, sent to the CDC labs in Atlanta, Georgia, would be
helpful. Have samples been collected outside Luzon? It will be also
necessary to find out if the ERV infection in the pigs had clinical effect
or was subclinical, incidentally discovered when sampled from PRRS-affected
pigs were tested in the Plum Island laboratory. - Mod.AS]
